properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 9 at 3:25AM HST until February 10 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
...HIGH WIND WARNING THROUGH 6 AM TUESDAY FOR THE BIG ISLAND
SUMMITS...
...WIND ADVISORY THROUGH MONDAY FOR KAUAI AND OAHU...
...HIGH WIND WATCH FOR HALEAKALA TONIGHT...

* WHAT...Northwest winds 25 to 30 mph with localized gusts over 45
mph expected.

* WHERE...Portions of Kauai and Oahu, with the strongest winds
near mountains, gaps and where winds blow downslope from higher
terrain.

* WHEN...From 3 PM this afternoon to 6 PM HST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down, and cause sporadic power outages.
properties.instruction:
Motorists should use extra caution.

Secure trash cans, lawn furniture, and other loose outdoor objects
that can be easily blown around by strong winds.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 6 PM HST MONDAY
